'''Nicolaus Copernicus''' ({{baso-pl|Mikołaj Kopernik}}; {{baso-de|Nikolaus Kopernikus}}; namo maso mudo, ''Niclas Koppernigk'';<ref>Nicolaus Copernicus Gesamtausgabe: ''Urkunden, Akten und Nachrichten: Texte und Übersetzungen'', ISBN 3-05-003009-7, pp.23ff. ([http://books.google.com/books?id=aEZrYxkjLkIC&pg=PA23&vq=Koppernigk&source=gbs_search_r&cad=0_1 online]); [[Marian Biskup]]: ''Regesta Copernicana (calendar of Copernicus' Papers)'', Ossolineum, 1973, p.32 ([http://books.google.com/books?id=3gkLAAAAMAAJ&q=Koppernigk&pgis=1#search online]). This spelling of the surname is rendered in many publications ([http://books.google.com/books?lr=&as_brr=3&q=Koppernigk&btnG=Search+Books Auflistung]) [http://scholar.google.de/scholar?hl=en&lr=&q=Koppernigk&btnG=Search]</ref> {{Lang-it|Nicolò Copernico}}; 19 Pebruari 1473 – 24 Mei 1543) saurang astronomi zaman ''Renaissance''<!-- no assertion of nationality here! see section on his nationality, the discussion page and Wikipedia:Neutral point of view --> dan urang partamo nan maajukan proposal formula nan komprehensif tentang ''heliocentris cosmology'', nan menempatkan bumi bukan sebagai pusat alam semesta.<ref>Copernicus was not, however, the first to propose some form of heliocentric system.  A Greek mathematician and astronomer, [[Aristarchus of Samos]], had already done so as early as the third century BCE.  Nevertheless, there is little evidence that he ever developed his ideas beyond a very basic outline [[#Reference-Dreyer-1953|(Dreyer, 1953]], [http://www.us.archive.org/GnuBook/?id=historyofplaneta00dreyuoft#148 pp. 135–48]; [[#Reference-Linton-2004|Linton, 2004, p. 39)]].</ref>

